        <h3>Lines</h3>
        <p>Braid is nearly always the way to go with any form of contact fishing, and it's lack of stretch gives immediate response from any biting fish.Madeira is largely made up of volcanic rock which will happily slice through your line, so strong mono or fluorocarbon leaders are essential, as much as to aid abrasion resistance as to the myriad of fighting fish that could be caught.</p>
